examples/support_bot/README.md
     1вҶ’# Support bot
     3вҶ’This example is a customer service bot which includes a user interface agent and a help center agent with several tools.
     4вҶ’This example uses the helper function `run_demo_loop`, which allows us to create an interactive Swarm session.
     5вҶ’
     6вҶ’## Overview
     8вҶ’The support bot consists of two main agents:
     9вҶ’
    10вҶ’1. **User Interface Agent**: Handles initial user interactions and directs them to the help center agent based on their needs.
    11вҶ’2. **Help Center Agent**: Provides detailed help and support using various tools and integrated with a Qdrant VectorDB for documentation retrieval.
    12вҶ’
    13вҶ’## Setup
    15вҶ’To start the support bot:
    16вҶ’
    17вҶ’1. Ensure Docker is installed and running on your system.
    18вҶ’2. Install the necessary additional libraries:
    19вҶ’
    20вҶ’```shell
    21вҶ’make install
    22вҶ’```
    23вҶ’
    24вҶ’3. Initialize docker
    25вҶ’
    26вҶ’```shell
    27вҶ’docker-compose up -d
    28вҶ’```
    29вҶ’
    30вҶ’4. Prepare the vector DB:
    31вҶ’
    32вҶ’```shell
    33вҶ’make prep
    34вҶ’```
    35вҶ’
    36вҶ’5. Run the main scripy:
    37вҶ’
    38вҶ’```shell
    39вҶ’make run
    40вҶ’```

